<Rate>1<//Rate>< text>
They closed the door in our face!!! When you get a confirmation email you get the address:
6498 East South Street
Lakewood, CA US 90713

"East" is a problem on their website.

Plug this in to Google maps and see where it takes you, it takes you 3 miles on the other side of South Street.
Nonetheless, that's not the worst part. When my wife and I realized the address was off, we called Hertz at 5:54 pm to notify them that we were just down the road, the woman on the phone said great, we have your car ready. I kid you not, I was at the door at 6:01 pm and they were inside ignoring me with the door locked. My wife drove to the back where they were running out of the store and said straight to my wife's face come back tomorrow, we open at 7. What kind of customer service is that? She said her name was Kay White, but who know if that was the truth. I am very upset right now considering this just happened within the hour.

Not even one star, I couldn't imagine treating another person that way....horrible.</text>

Renter BEWARE!!!. Read your contract prior to leaving. I was quoted a price for a four day rental; Upon my return ( 4 days later) I found that the price was actually for a three day rental. I was charged a late fee due to the paperwork I did not examine was for three as well. When making reservations ask for a proof email to verify what the actual agreement is for. ( They said all they needed was my name. ) Seeing you sign a screen and not paperwork any more be sure you view the rate and return time. This is how they got me. I signed and they tossed it in to an envelope and I ways on my way. The agent gave me a price for a three day to sway me from another company with a better four day deal. I should of gone with Alamo. If there was a score for less than one star I would post that. Be careful. I am not saying all Hertz locations are this way just be extra careful in Lakewood. Try the Long Beach Airport for safer options.<//Text>

I don't write a review a lot, but they don't even know what they need to do for the customers including a manager "Deannah". I've booked online a full size sedan for better MPG and comfort because my wife and I wanted to travel for a long distance. I've even prepaid for a weekly rate to reserve it for sure, but when we got there they rented all cars to auto repair shops and only one car Buick SUV was left for us...."Free Upgrade for us???" That's what they told me; they didn't even want to know what I meant for BETTER MPG. I wouldn't not recommend this place; not even 1 star but a minus 5 stars. The office is so small, and it seems like less than 5 cars in the parking lot. I don't understand what 2 or 3 Employees are doing in that small office.

< Text>
Super simple - no problems.

I used my AAA discount and got an excellent rate. I went to pick it up and the car was a little dirty from all the rain we've been having; they offered to take it to the car wash and vacuum it out; that took like 15 - 20 min but they told me upfront that it would.

Note: There were a couple of customers there that didn't seem very happy (don't know why) so i had some doubts at first -  but I had no problems at all.

The car looked and ran great on our little 300 mile trip. Dropped it off after hours and used the drop box for the keys. There were no surprises or extra charges. They don't have a huge selection of cars but I expected that because it's a really small place.

I will definitely use this Hertz location again the next time i need to rent a car.< /Text>

I'm pretty close to this place, since music is one of my passions. It's been around even before I was born, and my teacher's as well. It's what introduced me to learning guitar and later drumming, and the people there are chill enough to ask any question. Or just talk, I guess. Either way, definitely recommend coming if you need lessons or equipment.</Review>

< username>

1480628668518</Time>
< rate>
5< /rate>
< Review>
Hands down the best place to throw a kid party!

Our 5-year-old loves open play at this place. So naturally we knew Imagine Me Grow would be the perfect place to throw our youngest daughter's 1st birthday party. And boy were we right! It was completely stress-free and there was no mess to clean up afterwards.

We were allowed to bring in our own food/decorations; however, you can also purchase them through Imagine Me Grow. But regardless, the staff, which by the way, were the sweetest, helped set up our party decor and food/dessert stations. Oh, and they even took photos as well!

Also, most kid party centers do not allow you to bring in your own food so this was a major plus for us as our oldest has a couple severe food allergies.

But the best part of it all was that all of our guests had an amazing time. Everyone kept complimenting how fun and cute the place was. Some even mentioned they'd like to throw their next kids birthday party there.<//Review>

<Review>Wonderful fun play stations! We attended a birthday party here today for a classmate of my son. 4/5 year olds and their siblings were welcomed and allowed to play and explore. It reminded me of a  children's pottery barn catalog brought to life! Very sweet moments as my son and friends served one another in the bakery and sea food restaurant. My younger two loved the fire station very much. The cars can be pushed around the road and this was a please t surprise. The dance room was often empty but once in a while the children would enter and burst into dance. It was fun! Each room has a small screen tv with the rooms topic playing on the screen. At first I felt this was unecessary but as the party progressed it made sense, and had no sound so it wasn't intrusive to their imaginative play.

A music room would be fun, but trust me the kids were very satisfied and the play kitchens, fire station and dance room seemed to be my three boys favorite.

If I had to give any critique it would be to share that it is not a tactile/sensory experience as it is very clean and free of any sand or water play. That is understandable as it accomadates cooperative play amongst many children, young children. The environment fostered cooperative play and surprisingly allowed children the freedom to cooperate and play individually. I highly recommend!

In a time where children play centers resemble casinos and bars, and are often filled with video games this was refreshing!

Created for the younger child I find it sweet that they are not bombarded with flashing lights and bribery of candy and cheap toys. If my older kids were with me I could see them getting a little "bored" but I would encourage them to play and pretend with their younger siblings and I know the entire family would be better for it! So often we spend time and money to celebrate our children but we end up just consuming and teaching them greed and consuming. This truly fosters imaginative play that will help families bond, social skills flourish and develop life long memories.</Review><pictures>None<//pictures><Time>1457745779244<//Time>< name>
Meri Willard< /name>

<user>103766561348092093664</user>< Name>
Kareem Pinkston<//Name>
< time>
1408207936462< /time>
< Rating>
4</Rating>
< Text>
This was my first time to a Chinese establishment in San Diego; in Fallbrook no less. My fianc√© and I had a very unique experience here that suited the nature of this town very well.
The first thing we noticed is that the atmosphere and ambiance seemed truly authentic. It's almost like a hole-in-the-wall Chinese spot, but with finesse. The decor was traditional, the seating was cozy and the music was exactly what I'd expect in an authentic Asian location. The feel was very warm and welcoming.
We were greeted very friendly and with open-arms from an older lady (who appeared to be the owner), who was all-smiles and had a deep Asian accent. We then noticed it was only her and possible a cook in the back. This led to the true, authentic feeling of a "mom and pop" restaurant. Loved it!! I don't like "chain" food establishments.
With all this in mind, please be aware that your food is 'made-to-order' and takes its time to be prepared; so sit-back and read the papers or enjoy your conversation.
Now for the food. We ordered the Pu-Pu Platter, soup, a rice bowl and veggie pan-friend noodles.
The portions here are 'human-sized' and not the typical "American Super-Sized" kind.
My teriyaki chicken rice bowl suited me perfectly and the appetizers came in 2 piece samples. I wasn't used to how they prepared the pan-fried noodles and they weren't exactly "crispy" or slightly burned like I've had before; but I'm sure that's just their way of doing the dish. I'll go back next time and order something simple and use that as my basis.
All-in-all, I liked my dining experience here in this quaint, authentic restaurant.

Side Note: I wasn't immediately hungry when I got home and that leads me to believe they don't use MSG in their cooking. Yay!!!</Text>

<rate>5<//rate><name>Jays Fasheezy< /name>< text>
Prior to finding United Tires I was getting ripped off by all sorts of mechanics, things such as being overcharged, fixing things that didn't need fixing (you get the idea) When I came to United Tires I really thought these guys are too good to be true. My wife and I own 2 Honda Accords and 1 Ford Ranger and prior to that have owned other Honda's as we are a Honda family.

Alex, Ernesto and Alejandro are some of the coolest guys you want to meet. They treat you with respect and are very knowledgeable in what they do. My wife has had a complete overhaul on her 91 Accord (Great job guys). We also get our new brake pads, radiators, tires khumo , tune ups.....ect.

As I am writing this review I have my 02 Accord presently at their shop being worked on and I have complete trust in these guys and that's hard to find now days. I referred my old neighbor and he's still a happy customer to this day.

I'm not one for writing reviews only when it comes to my Jordan's but I have been with United Tires for around 5 or 6 years  and these guys work hard at what they do and they have earned this review through good customer service, work ethics and most of all integrity.

Plus their prices fit my budget! Couldn't ask for more. Keep up the good work guys and as long as United Tires is around and I have a car I'll keep coming back.

God Bless..............!

E. Strong...............!<//text>

< Review>
Went in, placed an order at 6:50, I was told the wait would be 20 minutes. I came back in at 7:10, pizza still wasn't ready. I gave my name and was told the wait would be 6 minutes more.
I sit down, and after trying to be patient and letting them handle the line, I finally get up and ask about my pizza. By this time it was 7:40, nearly an hour after ordering. After again giving my name, I'm told I need to show my receipt, which clearly means they have lost track of my order.
Without saying any apologies or even giving me any words at all, the employee goes to the back, leaving me to wait for several minutes without knowing what was going on. I could hear people arguing in the back over an order placed an hour ago, clearly mine.
Finally, a different person comes out and hands me a pizza. There were no apologies, no attempts to reconcile the mistakes at all.
Terrible customer service, absolutely no sense of urgency, and employees who were indifferent and had zero enthusiasm or friendliness.< /Review>

< Text>
This was my second time at this location, and I have been to the Santee and Oceanside locations a few times..
This particular visit was fantastic. Our waitress was very quick with the service, and to make it even better, the food was served beautifully and bountifully portioned. I have the membership, which is free, and receive frequent buy one get one free coupons emailed to me. It's such an awesome deal and it makes it better that the food is so good. The only downside is that like with all restaurants, you can occasionally get worse than average service and that is frequently the problem with the Santee location. This Mission Valley location is highly recommended. They were packed but still had everything available to us with impeccable timing. Just wonderful overall.< /Text>

< Review>
The restaurant is cozy and charming. I ordered the salmon omelette, which was delicious! The hostess and server were very friendly. There was a short wait to be seated and for the food to arrive but it was fairly busy. The parking lot is a challenge, the parking spots are small and the lot was almost full when I arrived. You might want to call for reservations and ride share if you are going as a group. Highly recommended for a cozy little brunch date.</Review>

< review>
She suggested Mimi's Cafe and I said sure.  I mean I've never been there, so I will give it a go.  Finding it was fairly easy, but parking... woof.  I lucked out, but my sister and lots of other people were circling that lot like vultures.  The wait for a table was long... long... and that's why I hesitate to give the fifth star.  When we finally got seated, they were kind enough to bring us a combination of breakfast and lunch menus.  Nice, but for an indecisive person... deadly.  In fact, I was torn... eventually I decided on the lunch menu, then I had to narrow it down from there.  I ended up with the Mediterranean Pasta with Chicken.  Our service was friendly, although we went through most of the meal without refills on any of our drinks, which was a bit of a bummer.

My pasta was delicious... not a whole lot of artichokes, but lots of sun dried tomatoes and chicken!  The sauce was really good as well, creamy, but had a lovely flavour.  I wish they had a half portion, because that would be just right.  Other things ordered at the table:  Chicken Pot Pie, Children's spaghetti, Pumpkin Spice Pancakes, and another breakfast dish.  Everyone ate their food and enjoyed it... my sister was in love with the pancakes and kind of made me wish that I had ordered them.  My nephew thought that he was going to need two entrees, but he didn't need it and it was a good thing he didn't order another dish.  My niece decided she wanted have dessert... and she narrowed it down by how much room she still had in her tummy... I wish I was that young and innocently silly again.<//review>

<review>Typical chain restaurant , but admittedly one of my favorites.  I love the menu here, the baked goodies, and overall ambience.  Our waitress was absolutely stellar even though she was practically working by herself as it was almost closing time.  Everything came out quickly and she made sure to check in on us regularly.  Only issue was that we ordered zucchini that was so oversalted that our mouths were watering and we couldn't continue eating it.  Luckily we were so stuffed by everything else we found no need to send it back or replace it.  I made sure to let our waitress know, and she was genuinely concerned and informed the kitchen to make an attempt to fix the problem.  Even though everything wasn't 100% perfect this time around, I would still definitely return to this location based on my overall satisfaction with Mimi's as a whole .  Bonus is that they offer military discount here as well as a ton of promotions from social media and their e club.</review></record>
